WEBVTT

00:01.002 --> 00:03.002
[ Upbeat music plays ]

00:25.692 --> 00:29.428
>> Class!
Time to hand in your homework!
>> Darwin: What are we gonna do?

00:29.430 --> 00:32.364
What are we gonna do?
If we tell her the truth, she'll
flip!

00:32.366 --> 00:38.470
>> Gumball: Be cool, buddy.
It'll be fine.
[ Slop! ]

00:38.472 --> 00:42.107
>> At least it's on time.
>> Darwin: I wasn't built to
take this much pressure!

00:42.109 --> 00:45.511
>> Gumball: Relax, man.
We'll just tell her what really
happened.

00:45.513 --> 00:49.681
>> All right, you two.
What's<i> today's</i> excuse?
>> Gumball: [ Clears throat ]

00:49.683 --> 00:54.820
Our dad ate our homework.
>> Rrrrrrrrrrr...
Go to the guidance counselor

00:54.822 --> 00:57.456
immediately!
>> Gumball: But, miss simian --
>> and don't come back until

00:57.458 --> 01:01.226
you've learned how to tell the
truth!
>> Gumball: [ Sighs ]

01:01.228 --> 01:05.864
>> And this is what the<i> inside</i>
of a liar looks like.
>> Both: Ewwww!

01:05.866 --> 01:10.769
>> Notice the dark abyss here.
That's the corrupt soul of the
liar.

01:10.771 --> 01:13.539
>> Gumball: But, Mr. small,
we're not liars.
>> [ Scoffs ]

01:13.541 --> 01:17.142
You should tell that to the last
boy that sat there and lied to
me.

01:17.144 --> 01:20.779
He's<i> there</i> now.
>> Darwin: The prison?!
>> No, next to it.

01:20.781 --> 01:24.383
>> Gumball: The cemetery!
What happened to him?
>> He just works there.

01:24.385 --> 01:28.387
[ Both sigh ]
Now, let me show you something.

01:30.623 --> 01:36.261
This is the lying hat.
Now, watch what happens when i
put it on.

01:36.263 --> 01:39.198
Your mother called.
>> Both: Oh.
>> She says she hates you.

01:39.200 --> 01:41.900
[ Both gasp ]
>> Gumball: She does?
[ Shatter! ]

01:41.902 --> 01:44.937
>> Darwin: I think my heart just
broke.
>> It's okay, kids.

01:44.939 --> 01:48.807
That was a lie.
[ Both sigh ]
But, you see, that's what a lie

01:48.809 --> 01:52.611
will do -- hurt your feelings.
She hates you.
>> Both: Ohhh!

01:52.613 --> 01:54.746
>> She loves you.
>> Both: Yay!
>> Hates you!

01:54.748 --> 01:56.381
>> Both: Aww.
>> Loves you.
>> Both: Yay!

01:56.383 --> 01:59.485
>> Hates you. Loves you.
Hates you. Loves you.
Hatesyoulovesyouhatesyoulovesyou

01:59.487 --> 02:03.255
hatesyoulovesyouhatesyoulovesyou
[ Both panting ]
so, what have we learned today?

02:03.257 --> 02:07.593
>> Darwin: Never trust a man in
a hat.
>> Yes, but what else?

02:07.595 --> 02:12.231
>> Both: Uhhhh...
>> Honesty is the best policy.
>> Both: Oh.

02:12.233 --> 02:14.900
>> Say it.
>> Both: Honesty is the best
policy.

02:14.902 --> 02:18.270
>> Good. And again.
>> Both: Honesty is the best
policy.

02:18.272 --> 02:22.941
Honesty is the best policy.
Honesty is the best policy.
Honesty is the best policy...

02:22.943 --> 02:26.812
>> Gumball: Okay, Darwin.
Remember, from now on, we only
tell the truth.

02:26.814 --> 02:29.748
>> Darwin: Okay.
Your face is too big.
>> Gumball: [ Gasps ]

02:29.750 --> 02:33.785
Well, when you say "s," your
gills whistle.
>> Darwin: [ Whistling ] You

02:33.787 --> 02:36.455
smell so stinky, sailors sing
sea shanties about your
stinkyness!

02:36.457 --> 02:40.359
>> Gumball: When you're asleep,
your face looks like this!
>> Darwin: When you're awake,

02:40.361 --> 02:43.295
your face looks like this!
>> Gumball: You walk like a
Princess!

02:43.297 --> 02:46.465
>> Darwin: You walk like a
pigeon!
>> Gumball: Okay.

02:46.467 --> 02:51.703
That's<i> us</i> covered.
Let's bring our honesty to the
world.

02:51.705 --> 02:55.207
>> Darwin: You've got a
monobrow.
>> Gumball: You've got no hands.

02:55.209 --> 02:57.576
Just being honest.
>> Darwin: Your face is burnt.
>> [ Gasps ]

02:57.578 --> 03:00.279
>> Gumball: I love you.
>> Darwin: But he'll never make
the first move.

03:00.281 --> 03:03.382
>> Gumball: Hm!
>> Darwin: He's having a party
on Friday, and he didn't invite

03:03.384 --> 03:04.783
you.
>> What?!
>> Sorry, man.

03:04.785 --> 03:10.722
You're just not cool enough.
>> Gumball: Whoa-ho!
This one is<i> long</i> overdue.

03:10.724 --> 03:14.059
Hey, Tina?
You smell, and it's not very
ladylike.

03:14.061 --> 03:17.663
>> Darwin: It's like a sweaty
watch strap.
>> Gumball: Nah, it's more like

03:17.665 --> 03:22.034
raw chicken and rancid milk in a
plastic bag.
>> Darwin: Yeah -- that's been

03:22.036 --> 03:25.804
left in the sun for a week.
>> Gumball: Okay, now that we
have your smelliness covered,

03:25.806 --> 03:29.775
let's move on to your
personality.
>> [ Growling ]

03:29.777 --> 03:32.311
>> Darwin: Ow.
>> Gumball: Yep.
>> Darwin: Ah.

03:32.313 --> 03:38.083
>> Gumball: The truth hurts.
>> Oh, Nigel.
>> Let's leave all this behind

03:38.085 --> 03:41.453
and go and live on a desert
island.
>> But how would we survive?

03:41.455 --> 03:47.593
>> On fruit, water...
And love.
>> Gumball: [ Clears throat ]

03:47.595 --> 03:50.796
Did you ask us in here for a
reason?
>> Yes, of course, watterson.

03:50.798 --> 03:54.199
I've been getting a lot of
complaints.
What on earth's gotten into you?

03:54.201 --> 03:58.370
>> Gumball: Principal brown, can
i be honest with you?
>> Uh, i -- y-yes.

03:58.372 --> 04:02.107
>> Gumball: I can't help
thinking that your relationship
with miss simian could be

04:02.109 --> 04:05.844
compromising your
professionalism.
>> Darwin: I completely agree,

04:05.846 --> 04:08.680
gumball.
And, frankly, i fear my
education is suffering as a

04:08.682 --> 04:11.617
result.
>> Gumball: And besides,
principal brown, you could do

04:11.619 --> 04:17.856
so-o-o much better than<i> that.</i>
>> Both: Rrrrrrrrrr!
>> Okay, so you got honesty

04:17.858 --> 04:20.659
wrong.
Perhaps we should try something
else.

04:20.661 --> 04:26.131
I'd like you to meet a friend of
mine.
Eh, one second.

04:26.133 --> 04:31.570
[ Grunts ]
Hello, children.
I'm the honesty bear.

04:31.572 --> 04:36.508
>> Gumball: O-Kay.
>> I'm here to explain that
honesty's not all black and

04:36.510 --> 04:40.379
white.
But, like my fur, it's more of a
gray area.

04:40.381 --> 04:46.118
Gray. See that? Gray fur.
Now, there<i> are</i> some things that
are "too" honest to say out

04:46.120 --> 04:49.221
loud.
>> Gumball: Honesty bear, I'm
confused.

04:49.223 --> 04:54.192
What<i> can</i> we be honest about?
>> Let me put this in a language
you kids will understand --

04:54.194 --> 04:59.298
hippity rap!
H-h-h-h-honesty!
Eh-eh-eh-eh-eh-eh-eh!

04:59.300 --> 05:02.134
Honesty!
Break it down!
[ Rapping ] ¶ when you want to

05:02.136 --> 05:05.971
be honest, just beware ¶
¶ truth hurts in this
nitrogenic atmosphere ¶

05:05.973 --> 05:09.141
¶ you got to wake up,
realize, and recognize ¶
¶ sometimes the truth

05:09.143 --> 05:12.778
has strategical lies ¶
¶ but keep them lies of a
manageable size ¶

05:12.780 --> 05:16.048
¶ or tears will arise
and hurt their eyes ¶
¶ so before you speak,

05:16.050 --> 05:19.351
it's best to remember ¶
each individual case will
require a specific judgment

05:19.353 --> 05:22.988
call, depending on who you're
talking to and the context of
the conversation!

05:22.990 --> 05:27.526
[ Ending note plays ]
Any questions? No? Excellent!
Goodbye.

05:27.528 --> 05:30.796
>> Gumball: Hmm.
Okay, i think i got it.
You should always tell the

05:30.798 --> 05:33.565
truth, unless you have to lie,
but if you do lie, you should
tell the truth about it, unless

05:33.567 --> 05:36.234
you're talking to someone who's
lying, because if they tell a
lie and you tell the truth,

05:36.236 --> 05:39.037
it'll be a lie because you were
lying about telling the truth,
inside of a lie, so the whole

05:39.039 --> 05:43.408
thing's a lie while still being
true.
[ Pop! ]

05:43.410 --> 05:46.812
[ Thud! ]
[ Sighs ]
Man, this "truth and honesty"

05:46.814 --> 05:51.483
thing is hard.
>> Has anyone seen the nurse?
I think my head may be on fire.

05:51.485 --> 05:57.389
Is my head on fire?
>> Gumball: Um...
W-would it be a good thing or a

05:57.391 --> 06:03.228
bad thing if it was on fire?
>> A bad thing, of course!
>> Both: It's not on fire.

06:03.230 --> 06:05.497
>> Oh.
[ Laughs ]
Whew!

06:05.499 --> 06:10.035
For a minute there, i thought my
head was on fire.
What a relief.

06:10.037 --> 06:15.807
So, how are things with you,
watterson?
>> Gumball: Uh...Yeah, not bad.

06:15.809 --> 06:19.277
You?
>> Pretty good, pretty good.
So, no more of that lying

06:19.279 --> 06:22.514
trouble, i hope?
>> Gumball: Eh...
[ Coughs ]

06:22.516 --> 06:26.918
No.
>> All right, then.
Toodle-oo!

06:26.920 --> 06:28.887
[ Alarm ringing ]

06:30.790 --> 06:36.361
[ Trickle! Trickle! Trickle! ]
>> Hmmmm.
Okay.

06:36.363 --> 06:43.802
Looks I'm gonna have to
introduce you to someone else.
I'd like you to say hello to the

06:43.804 --> 06:46.004
silence snake.
>> Both: Hello, si--

06:46.006 --> 06:55.280
>> silencessssssssss!
>> Gumball: B--
>> silencessssssss!

06:55.282 --> 06:59.384
Now, i bet your tiny minds are
thinking...
[ Dopey voice ] "But what if

06:59.386 --> 07:03.221
there's something important we
need to say?"
[ Normal voice ] Well, why don't

07:03.223 --> 07:07.726
you ask the silence snake?
[ Both whimper ]
Go on.

07:07.728 --> 07:11.897
He won't bite.
>> Gumball: O-Kay...
What --

07:11.899 --> 07:18.136
>> silencesssssss!
[ Both whimper ]
Well, it looks like my work

07:18.138 --> 07:20.772
here is done.
[ Sighs ]
W-w-whoa!

07:20.774 --> 07:27.746
Aah! Oh!
[ Echoing ] Uh...Boys?
Can you hear me?

07:27.748 --> 07:29.714
Say something!

07:31.217 --> 07:34.553
[ Both whimper ]
I think my knees are digging
into my back.

07:34.555 --> 07:39.858
You need to help me.
Now, there should be a little,
gold key on my desk.

07:39.860 --> 07:44.296
Oh, don't worry!
I've got it here.
Oh, gosh.

07:44.298 --> 07:47.566
Please, no!
Oh, wait! Maybe i can just --
[ Crunch! ]

07:47.568 --> 07:50.101
Aaaaah!
[ Both shudder ]
Okay, you need to get some help

07:50.103 --> 07:52.404
right now.
Right now!
[ Dialing ]

07:52.406 --> 07:54.940
[ Ringing ]
>> Elmore police.
>> Gumball: [ Inhales ]

07:54.942 --> 07:56.074
>> Darwin: [ Squeaks ]

07:59.111 --> 08:01.680
[ Zip! ]
>> Hello? Hello?
[ Sighs ]

08:01.682 --> 08:05.417
I'm sick of these prank phone
calls.

08:08.521 --> 08:12.991
>> Oh, it's just not the same.
[ Door closes ]
Oh, what<i> now?</i>

08:12.993 --> 08:17.963
>> Both: Mm! Mm! Mm-mm-mm!
Mm!
>> Eh-eh-eh-eh-eh-eh-eh!

08:17.965 --> 08:23.101
What's that supposed to mean?
>> Gumball: [ Sighs ]
Nyeah! Unh!

08:23.103 --> 08:28.240
>> Darwin: [ Grunting ]
[ Panting ]
[ Grunting ]

08:28.242 --> 08:31.676
>> What?!
Miss simian's trapped down the
old abandoned well?!

08:31.678 --> 08:35.313
I'm coming, my smoochkins!
Hup!
Aaaah!

08:35.315 --> 08:41.620
[ Groans ]
E-elbows, don't fail me now.
>> Gumball: [ Groans ]

08:41.622 --> 08:46.725
>> So, anyway, the plan is to
live on fruit, water, and love.
>> Dude, i don't care.

08:46.727 --> 08:49.861
>> Well, go back to fixing the
toilets, then!
>> Both: Mm! Mm!

08:49.863 --> 08:53.532
>> What do you want?
>> Gumball: Nyeah!
>> Darwin: [ Grunting ]

08:53.534 --> 08:56.167
>> What?!
I'm trapped down the old
abandoned well?!

08:56.169 --> 09:00.639
Oh, no!
I'm coming!
Aaaaah!

09:00.641 --> 09:04.142
Come on, chin.
don't fail me now.

09:05.611 --> 09:08.413
[ Thud! ]
>> Whoa-oa-oa!
Slow down, little dudes.

09:08.415 --> 09:12.617
>> Both: Mm! Mm! Mm! Mm-mm!
>> What's that?
Mr. small rocked back smugly on

09:12.619 --> 09:15.820
his chair, fell into the bottom
drawer of his filing cabinet,
it locked shut, and you want to

09:15.822 --> 09:18.290
use these crowbars to break him
out?
[ Both gasp ]

09:18.292 --> 09:23.562
>> Both: Mmmmm.
>> Aww.
See ya!

09:23.564 --> 09:25.931
[ Thud! ]
>> [ Echoing ] Aah!

09:25.933 --> 09:28.800
Oh!
Aah!

09:28.802 --> 09:32.137
Boys, i-i-is that you?
Do something! Anything!

09:32.139 --> 09:33.905
[ Clang! ]
Ow!

09:33.907 --> 09:37.876
Well, on the plus side, i think
that loosened the lock a little.

09:37.878 --> 09:40.712
Keep going.
Aah! Aah! Ooh!

09:40.714 --> 09:43.682
[ Gasps ]
Aah!

09:43.684 --> 09:46.751
Just a thought, but maybe you
want to lever the drawer open

09:46.753 --> 09:51.556
with that crowbar.
[ Both grunting ]

09:56.629 --> 10:00.298
>> Freeze! Police!
[ Gasps ]

10:01.867 --> 10:04.736
[ Clank! ]
You're coming with me, you
little hooligans!

10:04.738 --> 10:11.943
>> Gumball: But --
>> Darwin: [ Whimpers ]
[ Both sigh ]

10:11.945 --> 10:15.814
>> Why won't you talk?
Talk, darn it! Talk!
>> Mom: Officer, there's clearly

10:15.816 --> 10:19.317
been some kind of
misunderstanding.
>> Well, ma'am, looking at their

10:19.319 --> 10:23.955
rap sheet, it seems they are not
first-time offenders.
Multiple counts of antisocial

10:23.957 --> 10:28.593
behavior, vandalizing school
property, and setting their
principal on fire.

10:28.595 --> 10:34.399
>> And all because you lied
about your father eating your
homework.

10:36.602 --> 10:41.573
>> Dad: Okay!
[ Sobbing ] I did it!
Take me away!

10:41.575 --> 10:44.876
[ Sobbing ]
>> Why?
>> Dad: [ Sobbing ]

10:44.878 --> 10:50.148
I thought it was gonna make me
smart!
>> Well, it obviously didn't.

10:50.150 --> 10:55.253
So, i guess you boys didn't lie
after all.
>> Mom: Oh, I'm so proud of you

10:55.255 --> 10:58.523
two.
>> Both: Thanks, mom.
>> Um...One more thing.

10:58.525 --> 11:02.694
You don't happen to know where
Mr. small is, do you?
>> The only clue we could find

11:02.696 --> 11:07.165
was this sock.
[ Both gasp ]
[ Both whimper ]

11:07.167 --> 11:11.803
>> Oh, well.
Case closed!
>> [ Echoing ] This isn't funny

11:11.805 --> 11:15.240
anymore!
Can somebody please open this
thing?!

11:15.242 --> 11:56.381
>> Huh?
[ Music plays on headphones ]
>> He-e-e-e-e-e-e-e-e-l--

11:56.383 --> 12:00.552
>> dad: Bowls -- check!
Spoons -- check!
Cereal -- check!

12:00.554 --> 12:07.292
Oh.
[ Grunting ]
So much for easy opening!

12:07.294 --> 12:12.597
It looks so simple on TV!
>> Gumball: Oh, man, i really
don't want to go to school

12:12.599 --> 12:15.333
today.
>> Darwin: Me neither.
>> Gumball: Let's not go!

12:15.335 --> 12:18.002
>> Darwin: You can do that?
>> Gumball: Sure!
Hey, dad?

12:18.004 --> 12:21.272
>> Dad: [ Grunting ]
Yes?
>> Gumball: We really don't want

12:21.274 --> 12:24.409
to go to school today.
>> Dad: Why? Are you sick?
>> Gumball: Nah.

12:24.411 --> 12:27.278
We're just not up for it.
>> Darwin: Yeah!
School is boring!

12:27.280 --> 12:30.014
>> Dad: But you<i> have</i> to go to
school.
You're kids!

12:30.016 --> 12:33.151
It's what you do!
>> Both: Aw!
[ Doorbell rings ]

12:33.153 --> 12:36.621
>> Dad: Ooh! Mailman! Whoo-hoo!
>> Gumball: I wish we were
grown-ups, like dad.

12:36.623 --> 12:40.458
Then we'd never have to go to
school and nobody would tell us
what to do.

12:40.460 --> 12:44.262
We could drive trucks, stay up
all night, vote.
[ Both gasp ]

12:44.264 --> 12:49.300
>> Both: Vote...
>> Dad: Oh! Finally!
>> Gumball: What's that?

12:49.302 --> 12:52.137
>> Dad: [ Gasps ] Why?
According to the fifth
amendment, i don't have to

12:52.139 --> 12:54.739
answer that without my lawyer
present!
>> Gumball: Right.

12:54.741 --> 12:58.576
Anyway, about school...
>> Dad: Oh, yeah.
You're kids, so you do what mom

12:58.578 --> 13:02.680
tells me to tell you to do.
>> Gumball: [ Sighs ]
Being a kid is wretched-lame.

13:02.682 --> 13:06.718
>> Dad: You should be happy to
be young.
Before you know it, you'll be

13:06.720 --> 13:13.491
overweight, unattractive,
balding, middle-aged.
Take over breakfast!

13:13.493 --> 13:17.996
I don't want you to see me like
this!
>> Anais: What's<i> his</i> problem?

13:17.998 --> 13:21.733
>> Gumball: Eh.
You never know with that guy.
Come on. Let's have breakfast.

13:23.636 --> 13:27.405
Man, what a pile of beans.
>> Darwin: [ Gasps ]
Dude, watch your language!

13:27.407 --> 13:31.142
You'll get us in trouble!
>> Gumball: Well, I'm sorry,
Darwin, but it is.

13:31.144 --> 13:34.012
It's a big, steaming pile of
beans.
[ Whistle! ]

13:34.014 --> 13:36.981
[ Both gasp ]
>> Darwin: Gumball, look!
A shooting star!

13:36.983 --> 13:41.452
>> Gumball: This is our chance.
Make a wish!
I wish i was a grown-up.

13:41.454 --> 13:46.724
>> Darwin: Me too!
>> Gumball: They don't work at
all.

13:46.726 --> 13:48.493
Ugh!
>> Ow!
>> Gumball: Faker!

13:48.495 --> 13:52.964
>> Oh, darn kids!
What do you think you're doing?!
>> Today's lesson will be about

13:52.966 --> 13:56.801
the transformations of the human
body.
>> Gumball: [ Sighs ]

13:56.803 --> 14:03.208
>> As you get older, hormones
begin to change your appearance.
>> Gumball: Here.

14:03.210 --> 14:10.215
It's me as an adult talking to
my secretary over the intercom.
>> Darwin: It's me voting!

14:10.217 --> 14:14.586
>> Gumball: Awesome.
>> Passing notes, are we?
>> Gumball: No, miss simian.

14:14.588 --> 14:19.123
>> Well, then, what's this?
>> Gumball: Uh, that's us as
adults?

14:19.125 --> 14:22.227
>> I guess you're on topic,
then.
Anyway, pimples --

14:22.229 --> 14:26.030
>> all: Ew!
>> Silence!
Actually, it's pretty gross.

14:26.032 --> 14:32.003
You may continue.
>> All: Ewwwwww!
>> Pimples, or acne, can pop up

14:32.005 --> 14:35.273
at any time...
>> Gumball: Dude, what's that on
your face?

14:35.275 --> 14:37.976
>> Darwin: What? What?!
>> Gumball: That.
>> Darwin: What?!

14:37.978 --> 14:41.746
>> Gumball: It looks like a
greasy, yellow egg.
No, no, actually, it's more like

14:41.748 --> 14:44.849
a small volcano with a sweaty
golf ball.
>> Darwin: Do something!

14:44.851 --> 14:49.053
Do something!
>> Gumball: Okay, okay. Hold on.
Let me just, um...

14:51.724 --> 14:55.827
>> Darwin: [ Sighs ]
[ Pop! Pop! Pop! Pop! Pop! ]
>> Gumball: I think we're gonna

14:55.829 --> 14:58.463
need more little hats.
>> Darwin: Aaaah!
>> Gumball: Relax, dude!

14:58.465 --> 15:01.399
>> Darwin: That's easy for<i> you</i>
to say!
Why don't<i> you</i> have any?

15:01.401 --> 15:06.237
>> Gumball: Just lucky, i guess.
>> Darwin: Aaah!
>> Gumball: Aaaaaah!

15:06.239 --> 15:10.475
>> Both: Aaaaaaaaah!
[ Popping ]
>> Gumball: Oh!

15:10.477 --> 15:12.777
>> Darwin: Ow!
>> Gumball: Ew!
>> Darwin: Ugh!

15:12.779 --> 15:15.713
>> Gumball: I think that's all
of them.
What's happening to us?

15:15.715 --> 15:18.483
>> Darwin: I think we've got the
plague.
>> Gumball: Do you have any

15:18.485 --> 15:21.019
other symptoms?
>> Darwin: My top lip feels a
little silky.

15:21.021 --> 15:25.690
>> Next comes the appearance of
hair on the body and face.
[ Creak! ]

15:25.692 --> 15:28.793
>> Gumball: [ Laughs ]
